post_text: Attention all Genoa-Hugo parents and community members: There will be a presentation with Jamie Utt at 6;00 p.m. on Wednesday September 10th at the Genoa-Hugo School. The presentation will regard the bullying prevention program being introduced school wide, and anyone interested will be given immediate access to the parent training. You do not have to be there on Wednesday in order to use the training, but we recommend you go to learn about the program and get all of your questions answered. All students will be involved in the program as well, so going to the presentation will help you understand what your children will be doing this school year. Jamie Utt is a nationally recognized speaker, and this is a wonderful opportunity for you to see him in person. Hope to see you there!!!
text: Attention all Genoa-Hugo parents and community members: There will be a presentation with Jamie Utt at 6;00 p.m. on Wednesday September 10th at the Genoa-Hugo School. The presentation will regard the bullying prevention program being introduced school wide, and anyone interested will be given immediate access to the parent training. You do not have to be there on Wednesday in order to use the training, but we recommend you go to learn about the program and get all of your questions answered. All students will be involved in the program as well, so going to the presentation will help you understand what your children will be doing this school year. Jamie Utt is a nationally recognized speaker, and this is a wonderful opportunity for you to see him in person. Hope to see you there!!!

post_text: Construction needs to use a gas powered compactor in the new kitchen tomorrow in order to get the soil compacted and ready for a new floor. We tried it this morning but the gas smell quickly started spreading. Tomorrow morning they will be doing this again. We will seal off the area between the North and South wings of the building and any teacher on the South end will need to work on the North side. All doors will be open and should ventilate well without having an effect on the North side.
text: Construction needs to use a gas powered compactor in the new kitchen tomorrow in order to get the soil compacted and ready for a new floor. We tried it this morning but the gas smell quickly started spreading. Tomorrow morning they will be doing this again. We will seal off the area between the North and South wings of the building and any teacher on the South end will need to work on the North side. All doors will be open and should ventilate well without having an effect on the North side.

During the next 4-6 weeks, abatement of the following areas will occur: Shop and Shop Classroom, Mechanical Area above Kitchen, Hallway next to Shop and Kitchen, Cafeteria floor and stairs to gymnasium, and the Corridor from Main Entrance to Cafeteria
These areas will be sealed off and nobody is allowed to enter. Once the asbestos is removed throughout these areas, the cafeteria, stairs and hallways will reopen for use. The shop area will remain closed for construction throughout the entire project. SAFETY is the primary concern during this whole renovation and building project and help from the public to keep a safe distance from any area under construction is greatly appreciated.
The school district will keep an update of progress and changes on our website, Facebook page, and in the newspaper. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to call the school at 719-743-2428.
